I would like to have my windows with headers, but without borders, which is now 2 pixels. Is this possible?</description><pubDate>Tue, 04 Nov 2014 16:06:07 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4903/normal-window-without-borders/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Adaephon for &lt;p&gt;Hi guys, &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would like to have my windows with headers, but without borders, which is now 2 pixels. Is this possible?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4903/normal-window-without-borders/?answer=4907#post-id-4907</link><description>Yes, it is. Just set

    new_window normal 0

in your `.i3/config`

See [Section 4.8 in the User's Guide](http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_border_style_for_new_windows) for more information.</description><pubDate>Wed, 05 Nov 2014 08:12:54 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/4903/normal-window-without-borders/?answer=4907#post-id-4907</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Pietje for &lt;p&gt;Yes, it is. Just set&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;new_window normal 0
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;in your &lt;code&gt;.i3/config&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href="http://i3wm.org/docs/userguide.html#_border_style_for_new_windows"&gt;Section 4.8 in the User's Guide&lt;/a&gt; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
